DEAN v. DAVIS. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. January 27, 1915.) No. 1194. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the District of Virginia, at Richmond. Wyndham R. Meredith, of Richmond, Va., for appellant. Bartlett Roper, Jr., of Petersburg, Va., for appellee.

Before PRITCHARD and WOODS, Circuit Judges, and ROSE, District Judge-

PER CURIAM.

Decree of District Court affirmed. 212 Fed. 88, 128 C. C. A. 658. Appeal to the Supreme Court allowed.
